President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Thomas Rothman, Chairman of Tristar Productions, is nominated for Member of the National Council on the Arts. Peter A. Selfridge, currently Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of Advance & Operations at the White House, is nominated for Chief of Protocol at the Department of State. Douglas Alan Silliman, a career member of the Foreign Service, is nominated for Ambassador to the State of Kuwait. Robert A. Wood, Chargé d’Affaires at the U.S. Mission to the European Union, is nominated for the rank of Ambassador during his tenure of service as United States Representative to the Conference on Disarmament. Portia Y. Wu, Special Assistant to the President for Labor and Workforce Policy, is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Employment and Training Administration at the Department of Labor. President Obama believes these individuals will be valuable additions to his administration as they address the challenges facing America.